{"cursor":"4192","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Erica Eloff image = image_size = landscape =  alt = caption = background = solo_singer birth_name\n| = native_name = native_name_lang = alias = birth_date =  birth_place =\n| origin = death_date =  death_place = genre =\n| occupation = Soprano instrument = years_active =  label = associated_acts = website = notable_instruments =\n}}\n\n'Erica Eloff' is a South African soprano specializing in opera, lieder and\noratorio, currently residing in England. She made her professional debut in the\nUK during the summer of 2008 at Garsington Opera as Fiordiligi in Mozart's\n[[Cosi_fan_tutte|CosÃ¬ fan tutte]]. She also made her [http://www.wigmore-\nhall.org.uk/ Wigmore Hall] debut in their 2008/09 season with the pianist [http://www.ycat.co.uk/james-\nbaillieu James Baillieu] as a [http://www.kirckman.org.uk/html/eloff.htm\nKirckman Concert Society] Artist and made a critically acclaimed return in their\n2009/10 season.\n\nEloff graduated with distinction from the North-West University, Potchefstroom,\nwhere she earned multiple prizes and scholarships. She also won numerous singing\nprizes including the London\n[http://www.handel.cswebsites.org/default.aspx?page=19603 Handel Singing\nCompetition] (2008), the\n[http://www.unisa.ac.za/Default.asp?Cmd=ViewContent&ContentID=22106 UNISA\nNational Singing Competition] (2005), the\n[http://www.infoservice.fr/ufam/accueil/2004c.htm UFAM Concours Internationaux\nde Chant], degrÃ© Honneur (2003) in France, and the Singing Category and Overall\nwinner of ATKV FortÃ© (2000) (renamed [http://atkvprojekte.co.za/index.php?optio-\nn=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=231&Itemid=158 ATKV Muziq]). In the\nUK she was also selected by [http://www.makingmusic.org.uk/our-work/awards/award-for-young-concert-\nartists Making Music] as a Philip and Dorothy Green Young Concert Artist. Eloff\nhas been featured on BBC Radio 3's In\nTune [http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio3/intune/pip/0d3ch/ BBC Radio 3] and\ninterviewed by [http://www.classicfm.co.uk/on-air/presenters/bob-jones/ Bob\nJones] for ClassicFM.\n\nEloff works extensively as oratorio singer and recitalist in the UK, Germany,\nBelgium and South Africa and has also performed for various smaller opera\ncompanies in the UK. Her performance credits include Belinda in Purcell's [[Dido\nand Aeneas]], The Queen of the Night and First Lady in Mozart's [[ZauberflÃ¶te]]\nand Violetta ValÃ©ry in Verdi's [[La Traviata]]. She also understudied the title\nrole in Beethoven's [[Fidelio]] for Garsington Opera.\n","linknr":129,"url":"Erica_Eloff","recorded":1375056025,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Erica_Eloff&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Erica_Eloff&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","http://www.ericaeloff.com","/wiki/Soprano","/wiki/Opera","/wiki/Lieder","/wiki/Oratorio","/wiki/Garsington_Opera","/wiki/Mozart","/wiki/Cosi_fan_tutte","http://www.wigmore-hall.org.uk/","http://www.ycat.co.uk/james-baillieu","http://www.kirckman.org.uk/html/eloff.htm","/wiki/North-West_University","http://www.handel.cswebsites.org/default.aspx?page=19603","http://www.unisa.ac.za/Default.asp?Cmd=ViewContent&ContentID=2210